akas: Secrets of America's Favorite Places (original title)
akas from release info: Secrets of America's Favorite Places (original title)

1.title: Statue of Liberty

episode of.title: Secrets of America's Favorite Places (TV Series 2016– )

1.plot: Aside from the U.S. flag, there is no icon that is more identified with America more than the Statue of Liberty. Some little-known details story of how this statue came to be will surprise you.

2.title: Lincoln's Washington

episode of.title: Secrets of America's Favorite Places (TV Series 2016– )

2.plot: This episode explores secrets and mysteries of well-known and little-known structures associated with Abraham Lincoln in Washington DC. Are there secret messages contained in the statue of Lincoln at the Lincoln Memorial?

3.title: Mount Rushmore

episode of.title: Secrets of America's Favorite Places (TV Series 2016– )

3.plot: Mount Rushmore is one of America's most instantly recognizable national monuments. What did it take to carve the four presidents heads - sixty feet tall each - into solid granite?

4.title: Alcatraz

episode of.title: Secrets of America's Favorite Places (TV Series 2016– )

4.plot: What was it really like to do time on "The Rock"? One of the last surviving former Alcatraz inmates gives his first-ever TV interview and shatters many myths about the famous prison.

5.title: Golden Gate Bridge

episode of.title: Secrets of America's Favorite Places (TV Series 2016– )

5.plot: Get ready to see through the fog that often surrounds the Golden Gate Bridge and uncover the surprising stories behind the span.

6.title: Grand Central Terminal

episode of.title: Secrets of America's Favorite Places (TV Series 2016– )

6.plot: Grand Central's opulent design and beautiful space are explored in a search for hidden secrets - and there are three secrets contained in the main concourse's starry ceiling alone.

7.title: Hollywood Boulevard

episode of.title: Secrets of America's Favorite Places (TV Series 2016– )

7.plot: The show investigates how celebrities are awarded sidewalk stars. For the first time ever, the complete manufacturing of a Walk of Fame star is filmed from beginning to end.

8.title: Central Park

episode of.title: Secrets of America's Favorite Places (TV Series 2016– )

8.plot: Central Park is 843 acres, forming an oasis of green tranquility in the city that never sleeps. But how much of Central Park is made by nature and how much is engineered by man? You'll be surprised to learn the answer.

imdb.plot outline: This series explores the secrets, mysteries, and surprisingly little-known stories of some of the most iconic locations in America. Landmarks such as The Statue of Liberty, the Lincoln Memorial, and the Golden Gate Bridge hold secrets that few know about. This series reveals fascinating facts that will forever change how you think about America's favorite places.
